    • Field Detail

      • updateRunChecksums

        @Parameter(property="updateRunChecksums",
           defaultValue="true")
protected boolean updateRunChecksums
        Set this to "false" to prevent checksums from being persisted to disk. This is useful for "dry runs" where one may want to see the non-affected tests that STARTS writes to the Surefire excludesFile, without updating test dependencies.

      • cleanBytes

        @Parameter(property="cleanBytes",
           defaultValue="true")
protected boolean cleanBytes
        Set this to "false" to disable smart hashing, i.e., to *not* strip Bytecode files of debug info prior to computing checksums. See the "Smart Checksums" Sections in the Ekstazi paper: http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=2771784

      • filterLib

        @Parameter(property="filterLib",
           defaultValue="false")
protected boolean filterLib
        Set this to "false" to not filter out "sun.*" and "java.*" classes from jdeps parsing.

      • artifactsDir

        protected String artifactsDir
        The directory in which to store STARTS artifacts that are needed between runs.

      • depFormat

        @Parameter(property="depFormat",
           defaultValue="ZLC")
protected DependencyFormat depFormat
        Allows to switch the format in which we want to store the test dependencies. A full list of what we currently support can be found in
        See Also:
        DependencyFormat

      • graphCache

        @Parameter(property="gCache",
           defaultValue="${basedir}${file.separator}jdeps-cache")
protected String graphCache
        Path to directory that contains the result of running jdeps on third-party and standard library jars that an application may need, e.g., those in M2_REPO.

      • printGraph

        @Parameter(property="printGraph",
           defaultValue="true")
protected boolean printGraph
        Set this to "false" to not print the graph obtained from jdeps parsing. When "true" the graph is written to file after the run.

      • graphFile

        @Parameter(defaultValue="graph",
           readonly=true,
           required=true)
protected String graphFile
        Output filename for the graph, if printGraph == true.

      • loggingLevel

        @Parameter(property="startsLogging",
           defaultValue="CONFIG")
protected String loggingLevel
        Log levels as defined in java.util.logging.Level.
